text_copy_1853875258.text: Meet Altra's New elite trail Athlete, Careth Arnold

text_copy.text:
Careth recently moved to Durango, CO to further her pursuit of trail running which she found a love for in 2021. She found instant success and has graced the podium of several 50 milers. She entered her first 100k in Bandera and came home with a 3rd place finish. She plans to slowly increase her racing mileage and attributes her excellent race results to mom strength, perseverance, consistency, and a love for the challenge. 

03-7-2023

text_copy_copy_copy_1612682511.text:
Where are you from?

I am from my mother's womb - born into life in the back seat of a taxicab, stuck in Bangkok traffic. I spent the first 15 years of my life in Thailand before moving to a number of U.S. states.

text_copy_copy_copy__935922704.text:
How did you get into running?

I was an active kid who participated in a variety of team sports. I played soccer midfield, outside wing in touch rugby, and shortstop for softball - positions that all involve a lot of running - and I loved it.

text_copy_copy_copy__1370362781.text:
What do you love about running?

I love the persistent challenge, the views, and the sense of accomplishment that follows.

image.alt: JP holding up the peace sign

text_copy_copy_copy_.text:
What makes you excited about partnering with Altra?

Altra is setting a standard of inclusion by supporting and celebrating athletes from a colorful spectrum of experiences and passions.

text_copy_copy_copy__1644895230.text:
What running milestone are you looking forward to this year?

I am looking to expand my distance limits, prioritize fueling and recovery, and do harder things.

text_copy_copy_copy__1285042581.text:
What's your go-to Altra Shoe?

The Timp 4 - for everyday miles

the Mont Blanc Boa - for racing

the Rivera 3 - for road intervals/speed work
